#
CONSENT

Consent lets other players use spells on you that you may not want want them
to so be careful who you give consent to!

Also, giving consent to someone allows them to retrieve items from your
corpse.

USAGE: consent <name>   gives consent
       consent  removes all consent

#
"DAMAGED ITEMS"

The blacksmith will repair damaged items that are of type ARMOR not
all worn items are armor.

Damaged weapons can be repaired by puff
You CANNOT repair a weapon that has become damaged beyond use.

#
"FIND FAMILIAR"

Creates a familiar for a mage. can only cast once a day.
the mobs for this are not the best right now but i will add more.

#
WEAKNESS

Components  : ???

Can make your opponent weaker and do less damage.

#
"CHAIN LIGHTNING"

does d12 damage based on effective level (your present level minus the
level you learn the spell plus 1 (up to a max of 20)) to the mob you
cast this on and then 1/2 eff_level to the next mob in the room and
then 1/2 eff_level minus 1 to the next minus 2 to the next and so on.

#
"WARP WEAPON"
Components  : ???

Will warp a weapon and cause it to do less damage. A weapon cannot be
warped to no damage and this spell is aggressive.

#
"SLOW POISON"

If you have been poisoned use this to slow down the effects of it until
you can find someone to remove poison!


#
"AID"

Use this to save a person who is dying. It will not cure poison but it will
restore 1d8 hps and slow down their dying. This can only be cast on the same
person every 10 ticks.

#
KNOCK

Components  : lockpicks

Used to try to unlock a door.
#
"GUST OF WIND"

This spell will call into being a strong force of wind which will knock
anyone who fails their saves down.

#
SCARE

An attempt to scare a monster into fleeing the room (they can fail to flee
just like you).

#
"PWORD KILL BLIND"
Components  : ???

Power word blind will blind any mob under 100 hps

power word kill will instantly kill any mob under 120 hps.

#
"VITILIZE MANA"
Components  : ???

Will restore some of your lost mana, but not without some drain of your
life forces!

mana gain is ((dice(1, level)+20)*2)

you lose 100+ 2d10 hps and 25 move from the exertion of casting this spell.

#
INSURANCE

  Insurance will save you from a DT or possibly a death.
  If your wimp value is set higher than the damage from the blow that
  takes you below it (the wimp value) you will be rescued and spared a
  death.

  How it works:
  1) Buy a Token, you can only have 1 and cant give them away.
  2) decide on the hp value you want to be saved at. Set this with wimp #
  3) OFFER to see  what your "premium" will be if saved with present eq
  3) go play.

  When you fall below your wimp value you will be charged a premium and
  sent back to midgard. If you cant afford the premium your items may be
  confiscated. If this happens you have a chance to buy back your items
  until a crash or reboot.

  (Money is taken from your bank before your items are taken)

  Note: When you type offer at the insurance guy, he will by default list items
  worth more than 10,000 coins.  If you want to see lesser value items type
  offer value (ie offer 1000)
#
BATTER

   Battering an opponent with your shield enables you to stun an opponent
   for up to 4 rounds.  Although they'll still be able to attack, they
   won't be able to cast spells or use any special skills.  Be careful,
   thought.  If you fail, you'll be stunned and at your opponents mercy.
   Furthermore, you cannot try to batter someone unless you've equiped
   a shield and are _not_ wielding a weapon.

#
CHOOSE LAWS CORRUPTION

   The CHOOSE command lets you coose to be a law abider or a corrupted person.
   Once you have choosen your path there is *NO* turning back, so be sure it
   is what you want. You are given a chance to change your mind before its
   final.

   Consequences of choose:
   1) Once you have choosen, you can be killed by other people who have choosen.
      If you have choosen to be lawful, you may freely kill others who have
      choosen to be corrupted... You may not kill anyone who has choosen to
      be lawful.  If you choose to be corrupted, you may, kill, steal, and
      generally be a nuisance to those who have choosen to be either lawful
      or corrupted.
   2) PEOPLE WHO HAVE NOT CHOOSEN CANNOT BE KILLED OR STOLEN FROM.
   3) If you have not yet reached 10th level, you may not choose either
      path because it has been deemed that you are too inexperienced to know
      what is good for you :)
   4) You must  must have a perfect good or evil alignment in order to choose
      either lawfulness or corruption.

      THIS IS *NOT* REQUIRED. If you dont want to choose DONT.

      YES. This is all built into the code it is not even possible for someone
      to harm an unchoosen person or steal from them.

#
"HOUSES HOUSE"

   Houses allow the character who owns it to rent for free.  The character
enters the house, and types rent,and all the stuff is stored.  No one else can
rent in that room, just the owner.  Multi-room houses are legal.  Note:
  No 'gates' will be allowed, the house must be geographically correct.
(i.e. all entrances and exits must be close to each other).

  As a reward for godhood, Players who make godhood will be able to
purchase houses at a fixed rate (if they so desire) instead of the auction
price.

#
"MAYOR"

None

#
"RESURRECTION"

if the spell is cast on the corpse of a monster:

   That monster becomes a loyal follower of the caster, for 36 game hours.


