"STONE SKIN"
Components  : ???

   Stone skin makes your skin stone-like, improves your armor class
and makes you resistant to piercing attacks.

#
SPELL_INFO

How spells now work:
Spells do #d# * (your level+1 - spell learn lvl)  damage if its offensive.

Example: magic missile learnable at lvl 3 does: 1d4*1  if your lvl 3
 at lvl 4 it does 1d4*2 at 5,  1d4*3 and so on the highest multiplier
 on most spells is 20.  So the highest magic missile can get is 1d4*20

heres a list of all MU aggr spells

magic missile     1d4
shocking grasp    1d6
chill thouch      1d8*2  (not multiplied by lvl)
lightning bolt    1d8
burning hands     1d3
acid blast        2d8
ice storm         2d10
cone of cold      3d8
color spray       3d10
fireball          4d8
shriek            4d9
meteor swarm      5d8
mage fire         5d9

now for another example: say you just learned mage fire (lvl 125) it does:
5d9*1 you gain a level and it does 5d9*2  gain another 5d9*3  and so on up to 20


#
"SECTOR TYPES"
0 = indoors
1 = city
2 = fields
3 = forest
4 = hills
5 = mountains
6 = water (swimmable)
7  = river (non-swimmable.  must have a boat item to enter)
8  = air   (can't enter or leave without fly)
9  = water (can't enter or leave without water breath)
10 = fire (does damage)
11 = cold (does damage)

#
"CHARM MONSTER"
Components  : chunk of venison

Very similar to charm person, but allows you to charm monsters too.

#
"ANIMATE DEAD"
Components   :  mandrake        energy pill

  creates a zombie servant who will obey your commands.  It has
  your level d4 hit points, hits as a 2 HD monster, and is not
  immune to piercing weapons.  Cityguards and vampire bats hate
  zombies, and attack them immediately.

#
REFRESH

Components  : vitamin

  increases the targets movement by 1d4+1 per level, with a mininum
  of 20 points.
#
"SECOND WIND"

Components  : vitamin

  increase the targets movement by 1d8+1 per level.

#
TURN

   forces undead of lower level who fail their save against spells to
   flee from you.  The lower they are compared to your level, the more
   likely they are to flee.

#
SHIELD

Components  :  small egg

   creates a shield of magic around the target, some protection, and
   nullifies all magic missile attacks.

#
SUCCOR
Components  : mandrake, slice of pizza (dont ask)

   creates a word of recall scroll.

#
FIRESHIELD
Components  : ???

   different from D&D, creates a shield of fire around the target, and makes
   every attack against them do 2 * that damage to the attacker.  Similar
   to sanctuary in duration.

#
RACE

Various monsters belong to various races.  For example:
  Llama and rabbits are of the same race because they are
    herbivores (cows, horses, etc)
  Dragons are of the same race.
  orcs, gnolls, ogres, giants are all 'giant class' race.
  lycanthropes.
  predators (animals that hunt for food)
  undead
  snakes
  reptiles
  insects
  spiders
  demons
  devils
  humans, elves, etc...
#
"PICK LOCKS"

Thieves only.
For picking locks. Not all locks can be picked. Example:

  > pick door
  > pick safe

See Also : OPEN, CLOSE, LOCK, UNLOCK
#
SNEAK

Thieves Only.

Used for sneaking (moving in and out of rooms without anyone taking
notice).  When you type sneak, there is no way to know if you actually
sneak. If you successfully sneak, then you will continue to sneak for
a little while. When you are sneaking, many monsters that would
otherwise attack you will not notice you, allowing you to go places
that no others can get to.

Example:

  > sneak

See Also : HIDE
#
HIDE

Thieves and Assassins.

When you type hide there is a chance that you hide in the room. If
hidden you can only be "sensed" by the "sense life" spell. Even if
sensed your identity will remain hidden. Hide is broken by pressing
return, regardless of whether you typed a command or not.

Example:

  > hide
  Ok.
  >  (you wait for ex. 5 mins and remain hidden for 5 mins)

  >  (You pressed enter and no longer hide)
#
LOOK
For studying your surroundings. Examples:
look
look AT the angel
look IN the bag
look to the south   (or just: look south)

Note that if you LOOK AT CORPSE you will not see its inventory.
To see what is inside a container (e.i. Corpse) use LOOK IN <OBJECT>.

See also : EXAMINE or READ
#
AC

See: protection

#
PROTECTION

Protection information is shown like this:
Current Protection Information (ArmorClass/StoppingPower):
     Head: (100/0  )   Body: (100/0  )
     Arms: (100/0  )   Legs: (100/0  )
     Feet: (100/0  )   (Good: Low AC, High Stopping)

Saving vs.
  Paralyzation:   0     Breath:   0     Rods:   0
  Petrification:  0     Spells:   0     (Good: Low Saving)

AC is your armor value 100 is "naked" 0 is "well armored and -100 is a
"M1 battle tank" and very hard to get.

Absorb is the value your armor will take off of the damage from blows
(not spells) before you take damage.

Saving is your chance to not be or be less affected by spells and breath
weapons.

