SNOOP

Allows you to watch another descriptor's output.  You can watch several
descriptors at once.

USE: snoop <name>
     snoop Fred (you see all of Fred's commands and output)
>2008:     snoop <descriptor>
>2008:     snoop 10 (you see the input/output on descriptor 10)

Snoop with no arguments will stop all current snooping you are doing.

#
POLICE

Kills a user's link.

USE: police <descriptor>
     police 10 (kicks off char on descriptor 10)
     police <name>
     police Fred (kicks Fred off of whatever descriptor he's on)
     police -<site>
     police -132.28 (kicks everyone from domain 132.28 off)

Get the descriptor from users it's the first number.

#
PROMPT

Perilous Realms supports a flexible prompt system.. You can configure the prompt
however you like best.

We now can also support COLOR and multi line prompts and if you support true
vt100 you can have nonscrolling prompts along with whatever else you can dream
up.  SEE HELP CODES for a listing of some of the escape codes you can use.

Syntax:
	prompt 'format'
    or  prompt number

Using prompt number, you can choose a pre-made prompt.  For example, prompt 3
would give you a prompt just like PukeMud (Judy).  Prompt's 1 and 2 are meant for
immortals, and won't do much for mortals :)

With prompt 'format', format is as follows:
	Chacters in the format string not following a % sign are echoed back
out in your prompt.  The % is the prefix character for ceartain types of
substitutions.  Here is a sample prompt command line:

	prompt 'H:%h M:%m V:%v> '

Your prompt would then look like:
H:104 M:100 V:140>
Which mean you currently have 104 hp, 100 mana, and 140 movement points.

Here is a complete list of the % commands.  Case is IMPORTANT.
%h - Current hit points
%H - Maximum hit points
%m - Current mana
%M - Maximum mana
%p - Current power
%P - Maximum power
%v - Current Movement
%V - Maximum Movement
%o - Percent of maximum hp of opponent
%O - Name of opponent
%i - If you are invisible, this will be turned into a *, otherwise, blank
%l - Percent of maximum hp of leader
%L - Name of leader
%x - Current experience points
%X - Experience needed for level (negative if you can advance)
%g - How much gold you have
%G - How much gold you have in the bank
%% - tranlated to just a % sign

>2001:Immortal Only
>2001:%r - Current room number
>2001:%I - Invis level

There are also a few \ escape sequences:
\e - escape for making nifty prompts with color etc
\n - newline
\r - carriage return
\\ - echo a single \

Example prompts (using escape codes, this is not necessary it just makes them
look alot neater):

prompt '\e[47;31mH:%h\e[32m M:%m\e[34m V:%v\e[30m>\e[0m '   (H M V  in color)
prompt '\e[40;31mH:%h\e[32m M:%m\e[34m V:%v\e[37m>\e[0m '   (reverse of above)
prompt '\e[1mH:%h>\e[0m '      (hp in intense white)
prompt '\e[47;30mH:%h>\e[0m '   (hp on a reverse video background)

If you think you have made a neat prompt let use know and we will include it
in the prompt # stuff.
#
FLAGS

Let Deth or Alcanzar know if you need/want more room flags.

DARK             1
DEATH            2     Death Trap  *evil grin*
NO_MOB           4     Monsters cannot enter this room
INDOORS          8     MUST be set to avoid seeing weather
PEACEFUL        16     No fighting
NOSTEAL         32     No stealing
NO_SUM          64     No summoning from this room
NO_MAGIC       128     Spells, potions, etc... don't work here
TUNNEL         256     DOES NOT WORK -- DO NOT USE
PRIVATE        512     Can't teleport to, or goto if more than
                        two people are present
NO_GOTO       1024     Can't enter at all if not an Implementor
GOOD_ONLY     2048     Can't enter if NON-Good
NEUTRAL_ONLY  4096
EVIL_ONLY     8192
LORD_ONLY    16384     Can only enter if Lord or higher
RENTABLE     32768     If you quit here, you will keep your stuff
ARENA        65536     Makes room an Arena room.
FAST_MANA   131072     Mana regenerates quickly
FAST_HIT    262144
FAST_MOVE   524288
MAPABLE    1048576     Map command works at this location
NOSHOWEXIT 2097152     Prevents normal display of exits
FALL       4194304     Character forced to exit down unless flying
                       (causes damage)

To set multiple flags on a room using either edit fs or edit
addflag, simply add up the values of all the flags you want
and use that number.

#
XIT_EDIT

Syntax:  edit exit  <dir> <door flags> <key> <to_room> [keywords]
     ALL fields, except keywords must be present even if you dont
want a key.  If there is no key, set the key field to -1.  To remove
an exit (and the exdsc associated with it, if any), edit the exit and
set all of the fields to -1.

door flags are:

       NO_DOOR                0
       DOOR                   1
       DOOR_UNPICKABLE        2
       DOOR_SECRET            3
       DOOR_SECRET_UNPICKABLE 4

NOTE: secret doors ARE NOT detectable AT ALL by walking in the
direction they are BUT immortals will ALWAYS see them. SO you
*MUST* leave clues about the door or it will be useless, as no
one will ever see it.  If you want to create an exdsc (description
seen when a character looks in the exit direction), use
edit exdsc <dir>  You will be prompted for text. The <dir> field
must be one of the following numbers:

     0 = North, 1 = East, 2 = South, 3 = West, 4 = Up, 5 = Down
#
RIV_EDIT

     River rooms must be set using the river sector type (7) and the
                     edit riv <speed> <dir>
command.  You can't enter a river room without either fly or a boat item.
If you are flying, nothing unusual will happen.  If you are on a boat, you
will be forced to exit in the <dir> direction, and will see a message
saying "You float down the river..."  Needless to say, there must be
an exit going in the direction that your river flows for it to work.
#
TELE_EDIT

     Teleport rooms simply teleport anything/anyone (this includes mobs,
objs, and players) to the destination room after they a certain duration.
It is important to take into consideration that the real time it takes
between entrance and teleport will vary depending on how fast the machine
happens to be running.  If you want the players to see that they have been
teleported, set the <look-flag> to any non-zero number.  Setting it to zero
means that they will not notice they have been teleported unless they
specifically look at the room.

#
OLOAD

oload without a paramter transfers your workspace to your inventory
oload with a number loads that item into your inventory
to edit that item more you must ocreate old it again

NOTE: save your item before you oload it or you olose it ;)

#
BUILDING

See Deth for a building zone.

Please note that PR likes to have UNIQUE zones and prefers that if someone 
builds here they not share it with other muds. Give players a reason to come
see your area (mainly it not being on 2 or 10 muds) keep it to 1 mud if at
all possible please. (we will accept areas from other muds as well but they
would have to be very well done or "popular")

