CODES

Table of codes for use in Perilous Realms prompts:

Cursor movement:

	\e[r;cH (where r and c are row and column)
	\eD 	moves cursor down one line
	\eM	moves cursor up one line
	\e[#A	where # is the number of lines to move up
	\e[#B	where # is the number of lines to move down
	\e[#C 	where # is the number of lines to move right
	\e[#D	where # is the number of lines to move left
	\eE	moves cursor to beginning of next line
	\e7	save current cursor position
	\e8	restore saved cursor position

		Note:
			\e7 saves cursor position on the screen, not in the
			text. If the screen scrolls, the cursor will go to where
			the text WAS.

Text effects:

	\e[0m	Return to normal print mode
	\e[m    Return to normal print mode
	\e[1m	Bold text
	\e[4m	Underline text
	\e[5m	Blinking text
	\e[7m	Reverse video

Erasing:

	\e[0K	erase from cursor to the end of the line
	\e[1K	erase from beginning of the line to the cursor
	\e[2K	erase entire line
	\e[0J	erase from the cursor to the bottom of the screen
	\e[1J	erase from the top of the screen to the cursor
	\e[2J	erase entire screen

General Miscellaneous Codes:

	Make sure you know what you're doing before you screw with these,
	they can REALLY fuck up your screen.

>2008:	\ec 	Resets terminal (Not a good idea..)
        \e[t;br Sets scrolling region where t is top row and b is bottom row
			    Note: The top row and bottom row are INCLUDED in the
			    scrolling region..
>2008:	\e[r	resets scrolling region


	The following codes effect the entire line they are on,
	and can NOT effect a partial line.

	These codes are not recommended for the prompt itself, but for
	the "bars" on either end in a window..

	\e#3 	double height text (top half)
	\e#4	double height text (bottom half)
		Note: to make a complete double height word, use this

				\e#3word
				\e#4word

	\e#5 	standard width text
	\e#6    double width text


