#
SPLIT

Usage: SPLIT <# of coins>

Example: SPLIT 1234

The split command will split the number of coins given to it to everyone
in your group who is the same room as you.

You will get your share of the loot, and you keep anything that would be
left over by integer division.

For example, you are in a group with 3 people (so its you and 2 others),
and you just got 1000 coins from a kill.  So you type: SPLIT 1000
The other two people in your group with get 1000/3=333 coins each, and you
will get 334 (the one left over).
#
SCAN

Usage: SCAN

The scan command will look in all directions, and tell you who you can
see in those directions.

If you have the scan skill, you will be able to see further in each
direction.
#
FORM

Usage: Form lorange hirange

This command will bring into existance all rooms in the range you specify
(with at most 200 rooms at a time), so that you can link exits to them.
#
MAIL

Perilous Realms has a mail system based on mail daemons.  To send someone mail,
go to the Provisions Shop on buy a pen and a note, then type "write note pen".
It will then let you type in a note.  When you are finished, you can then
summon a mail daemon by typing "mail note Name", where name is the person you
want to send it to.  The note will be delivered as soon as the person logs on
again, or, if they are already on, instantaneously (them daemons are fast :)

Mail Rules:

  1) Junk mail, abusive mail, and mass mail is strictly prohibited
  2) If anyone sends the above, keep the mail, and report it... the
     mail is your only proof..
  3) Violators will be:
       Fined on first offense
       Deleted on second offense
       Have site blocked on third offense
#
"CHAOS NIGHT" ARENA

Every so often (pretty much at an immortals whim), an arena is run.  What this
means is that the immortal running it picks what levels he wants to participate,
and how much it will cost to get in, etc, and then the mortals are allowed to
kill each other, for a cash prize.  When an arena is started, a message will
be sent to all players telling them how to join, etc.

           ----- You loose absolutely noting in the arena. -----
When you enter, you will be fully healed, and when you are dead, you will
be healed and whisked back to the fountain.  Your equipment will not
be damaged, however, if you use limited use items (potions, scrolls, wands,
etc), they will be used permanently.  This will be fixed eventually though.

To be notified of what is going on in the arena type CHANNEL SPORTS, typing it
again will turn it off.

Asking for an arena to be run is a criminal offense, and you will be fined for
doing so.
#
HITALL

This skill allows you to hit everyone in a room.

If you type hitall all, it will attack everything in a room.
#
MAP MAPS

The map command will let you see a 5x5 grid around your area if you are
in Midgard.  There are maps of the city available on the board south
of the fountain, and there are map stones all over the place.
#
ASSASSINATE ASSASINATE ASSASINATION

To assassinate someone, you must be an assassin, and you must successfully
backstab them.  At that point, the game will make a check against your
assassinate skill (which goes up every 5 levels), to see if you got
lucky.  A level difference is calculated in, so that it is impossible for
a low level character to assassinate something well above him.
#
SHOPDOC

keeper
shopkeeper       Either one is acceptable... This is the vnum of the mobile
		 that is the shopkeeper.  This is required.

		 EX: keeper { 3020 }

location         Room number where this shop is located.
		 Eventually, if this is 0 (ommited), the mob listed as keeper
		 will be a travelling salesman.

		 EX: location { 3856 }

buy_type         The types of items that this shop will buy.  This is optional
		 and any number may be listed.  If nothing is listed under
		 this, and nothing is listed under buy, this shop won't buy
		 anything.
		 The following may be used:
		   light, scroll, wand, staff, weapon, fire weapon, missile,
		   treasure, armor, potion, worn, other, trash, trap,
		   container, note, liquid container, key, food, money,
		   pen, boat, audio, book, pouch

		  EX: buy_type { armor, weapon, key }
		  Note: This shop will only buy keys that are of type key...
		  Many keys are of type trash...

buy               This is a explicit list of items that this shop will buy
		  This is in addition to any it will buy because of buy_type

		  EX: buy { 1000, 1001, 1002 }

sell              This is the list of items that this shop will produce and
		  sell in unlimited quantities.

		  EX: sell { 100, 1002, 3004 }
		  Note that a shopkeeper will sell anything that he is holding,
                  so that he will sell anything he buys.

sell_mult         This is the markup for selling.  Should be >= 1.0
		  The selling price is computed as sell_mult*real_cost

		  EX: sell_mult { 2.0 }
		  This shop charges twice what things are worth.

buy_mult          This is the "profit" margin.  Should be <= 1.0
		  The amount the player gets is buy_mult*real_cost
		  Need not be listed if the store doesn't sell items.

		  EX: buy_mult { 0.5 }
		  This shop gives the player half of what something is worth.

hours             The hours this shop is open.  It may be repeated as many
		  times as needed to produce some weird hours.
		  If there are no hours listed, the store is always open.

		  EX: hours { 0, 3 }
		      hours { 7, 12}

		      Open from 0-3 and 7-12
		      
temper_player
temper_attacked  These are rather stupid, and if you know what they are for
		 you can use them if you want.(100% optional, and discouraged ;)
		 EX: temper_player { 1 }

messages {
	  dont_have { Message if store doesn't have }
	  no_item { Message if player doesn't have item he is trying to sell }
	  dont_buy { Message if shop doesn't buy item player selling }
	  shop_cant_afford { Message if shop can't afford item player selling }
	  player_cant_afford { Message if player can't afford item }
	  buy { Message when item is bought by shop... %d is price }
	  sell { Message when item is sold by shop... %d is price }
	}

Examples:
  messages {
    dont_have { Haven't got that on storage - try list! }
    no_item { You don't seem to have that. }
    dont_buy { I only buy armours.. Go away! }
    shop_cant_afford { That is too expensive for me - Try a wizard! }
    player_cant_afford { You can't afford it! }
    sell { That'll be %d coins, please. }
    buy { You'll get %d coins for it! }
  }


Full shop examples:

Note.. shop number has to be unique... Use a vnum in your room range...
preferably the room number the shop will be in...

4
{
  keeper { 3002 }
  location { 3009 }
  sell { 1001, 1000, 3030, 3031, 3032 }
  sell_mult { 1.5 }
  buy_mult { 0.4 }
  buy_type { light, container, food, trash, treasure }
  messages {
    dont_have { Haven't got that on storage - try list! }
    no_item { You don't seem to have that. }
    dont_buy { I don't buy THAT,... Try another shop. }
    shop_cant_afford { I can't afford such a treasure. }
    player_cant_afford { You can't afford it! }
    sell { That'll be %d coins, please. }
    buy { You'll get %d coins for it! }
 }
}



5
{
  sell { 3040, 3042, 3044, 3076, 3081 }
  sell_mult { 1.0 }
  buy_mult { 0.5 }
  buy_type { armor }
  messages {
    dont_have { Haven't got that on storage - try list! }
    no_item { You don't seem to have that. }
    dont_buy { I only buy armours.. Go away! }
    shop_cant_afford { That is too expensive for me - Try a wizard! }
    player_cant_afford { You can't afford it! }
    sell { That'll be %d coins, please. }
    buy { You'll get %d coins for it! }
  }
  keeper { 3004 }
  location { 3108 }
}

2
{
  keeper { 3040 }
  location { 3076 }
  sell { 3000, 3001 }
  sell_mult { 1.1 }
  messages {
    no_item { I don't buy! }
    dont_buy { I don't buy! }
    dont_have { It's very noisy in here, what did you say you wanted to buy? }
    player_cant_afford { Are you drunk or what ?? - NO CREDIT! }
    sell { That'll be - say %d coins. }
  }
}

#
SHOW

The show command is quite versatile.  The possible uses are:

  show zones
      Shows all of the zones in the game, their lifespan and age,
      (sometimes) who they 'belong' to, what range of rooms they include,
      and how often they reset.

  show (objects|mobiles) (zone#|name)
      Shows all of the mobs or objects within a zone, or all the mobs or
      objects that have <name> in their namelist.
  show rooms (zone#|death|private)
      Lists all of the rooms in a zone, all of the death rooms (DTs)
      currently in the world, or all of the private rooms currently in the
      world.

  show exits (zone)
      Same as above, but lists all of the exits instead of the rooms.
#
DEFAULTSPELL

How spells using this formula work:

Spells do #d# * (your level+1 - spell learn lvl)  damage.

Example: magic missile learnable at lvl 3 does: 1d4*1  if your lvl 3
 at lvl 4 it does 1d4*2 at 5,  1d4*3 and so on the highest multiplier
 on most spells is 20.  So the highest magic missile can get is 1d4*20

now for another example: say you just learned mage fire (lvl 125) it does:
5d9*1 you gain a level and it does 5d9*2  gain another 5d9*3  and so on up to 20

#
PORTAL
Components  :  a mithril hammer  and ???

Create a portal anyone can enter to a person
duration is level / 100 ticks

usage: cast 'portal' name

BEWARE: portals can lead to NASTY places you should probably look portal
first if you dont know where it goes. Newbies probably should not enter
portals.

#
RUNNINGLOG

The runninglog command toggles the log messages which normally appear on 
the screen. These messages include errors in the game, new characters
starting up, old characters logging in, characters logging out, and other
such details which can affect the game.
 
#
PWHERE

Pwhere allows an immortal to see where visible players are at that point
in the game. The format is: Pwhere [character's name]. This will give the
room number and room name where the player is currently located. The command
will also show where a visible immortal is.

#
SNOWBALL

Snowball is a harmless command, much like slap, whose use is limited to
immortals. The form is: snow(ball) [character's name], and the message
shown is: You conjure a snowball from the thin air and throw it at [char
name].

#
MWHERE

The mwhere command is much like the pwhere command, except that it shows
the locations of monsters instead of players in the game. The format is
also the same: mwhere [name].

#
OFFSET

Offset is a builder's aid command. If you are editing an area say in the
range of 250001 to 250099, then by typing: offset 250000 the range will
become 1 to 99. Basically it will add the offset value to any goto's or
at commands you use. To reset to no offest, use: offset 0.

#
RESCUE

A rescue is an attempt to put yourself between a monster and the character
who is currently fighting it. This means that, if successful, the monster
will now attack you. Only one person may be rescued per round. This is a
very useful command when playing in groups.

#
WORLD

The world command shows the most recent start-up time, current time at 
the source location, # of rooms in the world, # of zones in the world, 
facts and figures on mobs and objs, and the # of registered players.

#
SKILLS

The skills command will show all of the skills and the levels at which
they are gained. The format is: skills [class]. If you wish to see your 
own skills, no class needs to be entered. See also the SPELLS command.

#
SPELLS

The spells command will show all of the spells and the levels at which they
are gained. The format is: spells [class]. If you wish to see your own spells
list, no class needs to be entered. See also the SKILLS command.

For the old spells damage list see SPELL_INFO.

#
CHANGES
 
New class names:
W/T=Highwayman ------T/W=Rogue
M/T=Powermonger -----T/M=Scout
C/W=Templar ---------W/C=Expositor
M/C=Necromancer -----C/M=Scholar
R/D=Forester --------D/R=Herbalist
M/W=Warlock ---------W/M=Warlord
M/T/W=Overlord ----- M/W/T=Sohei
T/W/M=Brigand -------T/M/W=Dragoon
W/T/M=Mercenary -----W/M/T=Warder
W/D=Celtic ----------D/W=Woodsman
 
NOTE: PURE CLASSES get skills FASTER cheaper and BETTER
The FIRST class of a PC gets things better and FASTER
the SECOND gets SLOWER than FIRST class and NOT AS GOOD
the THIRD gets SLOWER than SECOND class and NOT AS GOOD
 
You now get between 50 and ~300 practices per level each practice is sort of
like a percentage point.
 
Spells now have DIFFICULTY levels SECOND AND THIRD "classes"  skills and
spells are more difficult to learn
 
A DIFFICULTY level of 1 means it takes 100 practices to get to 100% (assuming
you can get 100%). A DIFFICULTY level of 2 means it takes 200 and so on.
 
SOME spells and skills now COST CASH to learn.
Cost is figured: cost*diff*100
IE a cost 10 diff 1 would cost: 10*1*100 or 1000 coins.
 
You can PRACTICE # SKILL (or spell). IE prac 100 bash (is 100 bash sessions)
 
Check the Skill and Spell commands allspell doesnt exist anymore.
 
*IF YOU DIE YOU WILL LOSE LEVELS NOW! (and hps) exp lose has been lessened
to a max of 500k per 30 levels OR 1/4th exp if you have less than 500k*

Some spells take COMPONENTS now some of these will be in the help others you
must find on your own. There are only 2 right now many more will be added later
you need a bandaid for aid (for a few classes) and poison ivy for poison.

